      id: 69
      max: 3/1
      obj: Open `"test.txt"` in read mode and print its content using `f.read()`.
      expl: '`"r"` mode opens a file for reading, and `read()` returns its contents as a string.'
      sol: "with open(\"test.txt\", \"r\") as f:\n    print(f.read())"
      start: ''
    - name: Append to a File
      hint: Use mode `"a"`.
      files:
