    - name: Count File Lines
      hint: Use `len(f.readlines())`.
      files:
        initial:
          notes.txt: 'Line 1

            Line 2

            Line 3'
      id: 72
      max: 3/1
      obj: Open `"notes.txt"` and print how many lines it contains.
      expl: Files and lists can work together. `readlines()` returns a list, so `len()` can count its items.
