      id: 90
      max: 16/1
      obj: Read a string, an integer, and a float. Print each value followed by its type using `type()`. Then convert each
        variable to the other two types using `int()`, `float()`, `str()`, and `bool()`. Print a blank line between each group.
        Show `True` or `False` for boolean conversions.
      sol: 'a = input()

        b = int(input())

        c = float(input())

        print(f"{a} {type(a)}")

        print(int(float(a)) if a.replace(".", "", 1).lstrip("-").isdigit() else "N/A")

        print(float(a) if a.replace(".", "", 1).lstrip("-").isdigit() else "N/A")

        print(bool(a))

        print()

        print(f"{b} {type(b)}")

        print(str(b))

        print(float(b))

        print(bool(b))

        print()

        print(f"{c} {type(c)}")

        print(int(c))

        print(str(c))

        print(bool(c))'
      start: ''
