      - in:
        - '65'
        - '70'
        - 'no'
        exp: 'Fail

          '
      - in:
        - '-5'
        - '50'
        - 'no'
        exp: 'Invalid

          '
      id: 92
      max: 10/1
      obj: 'Read a score (int) and a passing threshold (int). Use `if/elif/else` with `and`/`or`: if score ≥ 90 print `"Excellent"`,
        elif score ≥ threshold and score < 90 print `"Pass"`, elif score < threshold and score >= 0 print `"Fail"`, else print
        `"Invalid"`. Also read a string `bonus` - if `"yes"` and score ≥ threshold, print `"With Bonus"`. Use nested `if`
        inside `elif` for the bonus check.'
      sol: "score = int(input())\nthreshold = int(input())\nbonus = input()\n\nif score >= 90:\n    print(\"Excellent\")\n\
        elif score >= threshold:\n    print(\"Pass\")\n    if bonus == \"yes\":\n        print(\"With Bonus\")\nelif score\
        \ >= 0:\n    print(\"Fail\")\nelse:\n    print(\"Invalid\")"
      start: ''
