      id: 93
      max: 16/1
      obj: 'Read an integer `n` (1-9). Use nested `for` loops and `range()` to print: (1) a right triangle of numbers where
        row i has numbers 1 to i, (2) a blank line, (3) a countdown using a `while` loop from `n` down to 1, (4) a blank line,
        (5) odd numbers from 1 to `2*n` using `continue` to skip evens, (5) stop if `2*n > 12` using `break`.'
      sol: "n = int(input())\n\nfor i in range(1, n + 1):\n    for j in range(1, i + 1):\n        print(j, end=\"\")\n   \
        \ print()\n\nprint()\n\ni = n\nwhile i >= 1:\n    print(i)\n    i -= 1\n\nprint()\n\nfor i in range(1, 2 * n + 1):\n\
        \    if i % 2 == 0:\n        continue\n    if i > 12:\n        break\n    print(i)"
      start: ''
    - name: Data Architect
      example:
        input:
        - '3'
