      id: 98
      max: 16/1
      obj: Read two integers `a` and `b`, then an operator string (+, -, *, /). Use `try/except` to catch `ValueError` (print
        `"Invalid int"`), `ZeroDivisionError` (print `"Divide by zero"`), and any other `Exception` (print `"Unknown error"`).
        Add a `finally` block that always prints `"Done"`. Use `if/elif` to apply the correct operation. For invalid operators,
        raise a custom `Exception`.
      sol: "try:\n    a = int(input())\n    b = int(input())\n    op = input()\n    if op == \"+\":\n        print(a + b)\n\
        \    elif op == \"-\":\n        print(a - b)\n    elif op == \"*\":\n        print(a * b)\n    elif op == \"/\":\n\
        \        print(a / b)\n    else:\n        raise Exception(\"Invalid operator\")\nexcept ValueError:\n    print(\"\
        Invalid int\")\nexcept ZeroDivisionError:\n    print(\"Divide by zero\")\nexcept Exception:\n    print(\"Unknown error\"\
        )\nfinally:\n    print(\"Done\")"
      start: ''
    - name: Module Alchemist
      example:
        input:
        - '5'
        - Hero
        output: '78.53981633974483

